support.p: Parchment. Fol. 1r appears as if it is a pamimpsest.

supportDesc.foliation: Foliated in the upper right hand corners of the rectos.

condition.p: The manuscript is in good condition. A top part of fol. 56 is, however, cut out.

layout.p: Written in one column with wide margins.

decoDesc.decoNote: Red and blue-green initials with pen-flourishing in the opposite colour.

physDesc.accMat: An AM-slip in Árni Magnússon's hand, pasted to the upper board, reads: Til foræring af Juſtitsraad Reitzer, men hand fick ex Bibliotheca Gudii ſi rectè memini Fra Fabricius I Hamborg fick hand bogen. Maa have været ex Bibliotheca Gudii Imò. Den er ex Bibliotheca Gudii .

history.provenance: The manuscript belonged to the librarian and manuscript collector Marquard Gude.
history.acquisition: Árni Magnússon was interested in Gautier de Chatillon's text as a source for Alexanders saga, and when Christian Reitzer made himself acquainted with Árni Magnússon's interest in the text, he or Hans Gram passed this information on to their correspondent in Hamburg, Johann Albert Fabricius. Fabricius purchased AM 825 4to on Marquard Gude's auction in Hamburg, 1709 and subsequently sent it to Reitzer, who in his turn, delivered it to Árni Magnússon.
